						<summary>

						<p>On a slab fixed into the celling of the Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Kali 4953, Śālivāhana śaka 1775, Paridhāvin, corresponding to 1853 A.D. Pramādīcha could be the cyclic year, and it lasts upto 9th March, 1853. In the A.R. for 1955-56, the Kali year was wrongly noted as 4653.</p>						

						<p>[Seems to state that the <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> was built or renovated on the specified date.]</p>						

						</summary>
